keyValuePair.Value: Are you ready for the Champions League?
Are you ready for the Champions League?
It's been a great season, Mr %1s. One win away from a Champions League spot. And one game to go. Are you confident your team can get the job done?
It's been a great season, Ms %1s. One win away from a Champions League spot. And one game to go. Are you confident your team can get the job done?
I trust this team.
The boys have been great this season. They're experienced, reliable, strong-willed. I think those are the qualities that can get us the win we need today. They deserve Champions League football.
The boys have been great this season. They're experienced, reliable, strong-willed. I think those are the qualities that can get us the win we need today. They deserve Champions League football.
It's up to the players now.
We've prepared well. I've tried to take the pressure off the lads as much as possible. They know what's at stake. And they know what we need to do to get where we all want to be.
I am confident the boys will stay focused and clinch it after the next game. And we have a few more games to improve our position even further.
Better late than never!
If I'm honest, I'd say I don't think it should be down to this last game. We should already have qualified. We'll have to improve if we want to do anything in Europe next season, that's for sure.
Are you looking good for a Champions League spot?
All you need to do in your next game is avoid defeat and you'll be sure of a place in next season's Champions League. After coming this far, you won't let it slip now, will you?
We're desperate for Champions League football.
I'm feeling pretty confident. Every time this team has been asked a question this season, they've found an answer. They just have to do that one more time today and we'll be there.
The boys won't need a team talk.
Everybody at the club knows what Champions League football would mean. The players definitely understand what's at stake today. They're ready to go out and grab their chance, I promise.
Why have we left it so late?
I feel nervous. We should have qualified long before now. But we are where we are. Let's get the job done, and then start getting ready for the challenge of the Champions League.
Feeling good about getting over the line?
Feeling good about getting over the line?
That must be a great feeling. Your team didn't let you down and got the result you needed to tie up a Champions League spot. You must be pleased how things have turned out?
That must be a great feeling. Your team didn't let you down and got the result you needed to tie up a Champions League spot. You must be pleased how things have turned out?
The lads have made the season special.
Champions League football will make such a difference to this club. And I know the supporters will enjoy the adventure. Well done to the lads for making it happen.
We're where we want to be.
Champions League football was the target this season. The boys have managed to clinch that. But we have to look forward. This is just one step towards where the club wants to be.
Now the real work starts!
Of course we'll celebrate. But not for long! There's work to do. Playing Champions League next season will mean a huge step up in class for all of us. We have to be ready.
How have you missed out?
You looked nailed-on for a Champions League spot. But everything went wrong for your team today and you've missed out. What happened to your boys when it mattered?
This has to push us on in the future.
I think today's disappointment will haunt the players for some time. It should. But I don't want to see them feeling sorry for themselves. What today feels like has to drive us all on to be better.
It's a blow for the club, that's for sure.
That was a really poor performance. We just never got going in the game and we've paid a heavy price. It's a massive blow to this club's ambitions.
We put pressure on ourselves today.
Look, it's a long season. We made plenty of mistakes along the way and they've cost us. It's why we found ourselves under pressure today. And, really, it's why we've missed out.
How big a blow is that to your ambitions?
You were within touching distance of a Champions League spot but failed to get the win that you needed today. How big a blow is that to your plans and the club's ambitions?
We have to make this a positive.
Everybody's down. It's a disaster. But we have to find the positive from what's happened today. For every player, this has to be the motivation to take us further in future.
We've missed a golden opportunity.
You can do everything right all season, but that makes no difference on a day like today. I'm afraid some of my players just froze. They weren't strong enough when it really mattered.
We can't just blame today's result.
Over the season, we missed plenty of chances to make sure of qualifying. We didn't take them and that's really why we've found ourselves missing out on our dream today.
Proud your boys have made Champions League?
Proud your boys have made Champions League?
It's been a long road to get here but, finally, thanks to today's win, you've reached next season's Champions League. You must be proud of your team?
It's been a long road to get here but, finally, thanks to today's win, you've reached next season's Champions League. You must be proud of your team?
We've delivered.
We set out at the start of the season with reaching the Champions League as our target. We left it till late, but we've done it. I think the players deserve credit for what they've achieved.
The boys are a credit to the club.
This team has fought for every point all season long. And, when it came to the last-gasp finish, they found the result that we needed. I think they've done this club proud.
Now we have to be ready for the challenge.
Reaching the Champions League is a good achievement from the players. But this has to be only the start. We'll have to work hard now and improve if we want to be competitive next season.
